content.description: Start up chossy rock and onto a good smooth face with a few drill scars and holes. Clip 7 new bolts and finish at a two bolt anchor. (Multiple large blocks about to come down at the very end of the climb. The blocks seem to be getting worse and multiple large blocks about to come down at the very end of the climb and possibly end will end up on the highway.
content.protection: This route is protected by 7 bolts and a 2 bolt anchor.

content.description: This route climbs the corner 6' right of the sport route.  Bring gear that will fit in the drilled out blast holes along with a standard.  Climb past one bolt lower on the route.  This climb shares the last bolt and anchor with the sport climb to its left.
content.protection: Let's Draw Allah is protected by trad gear to 3", 2 bolts and a 2 bolt anchor.

content.description: A road cut area that is directly along the highway.  A lot of the routes climb the old scars left by the drills when they were building the highways.  Mainly a top rope area unless you like climbing dynamite blast holes with cams and nuts.  Most belay off the telephone pole/trees up top.  Bring extra webbing to set this up.
